casebody.data:
Maude Thomas vs. Joseph Reder. Essex. February 5, 1930. February 6, 1930.

Present: Rugg, C.J., Pierce, Wait, Sanderson, & Field, JJ.

*354J. A. O’Mahoney, for the defendant, submitted a brief. No argument nor brief for the plaintiff. By the Court.

The report in the present case discloses no question of law but only questions of fact. The decision of the trial court on the facts is decisive against the contentions of the defendant. There is no occasion to discuss or even refer to the cases cited by the defendant. They are inapplicable to the case as presented.

Order dismissing report affirmed.
